## Option B: Full Stack Mode (Docker required)

### Step 1 – Start Docker containers

Open Terminal (`Tools → Terminal`):
```bash
cd "c:\Users\Hp\OneDrive\Desktop\ANTIGRATIVY TESTS\Payment Processing Microservice"
docker compose up -d
```

Wait ~30 seconds, then verify:
```bash
docker ps
```
You should see 3 containers: `payments-db`, `payments-redis`, `payments-mq`

### Step 2 – Configure your Stripe key

1. Open `src/main/resources/application.properties` in NetBeans editor
2. Replace the placeholder:
   ```properties
   stripe.api.key=sk_test_YOUR_ACTUAL_KEY_HERE
   ```
   > Get test key from: https://dashboard.stripe.com/test/apikeys

### Step 3 – Run the application (default profile)

- Remove the `mock` profile from project properties (`Project Properties → Actions → Run project`)
- Press `F6`

### Step 4 – Stop Docker when done

```bash
docker compose down
```

